[_The Latin Americanist_](http://ourlatinamerica.blogspot.com/2010/10/mario-
vargas-llosa-wins-nobel-award.html)reports: “This morning, Peru's Mario Vargas
Llosa was announced as the winner of the 2010 Nobel Prize in Literature.
According to the Nobel Prize's website the journalist, essayist, and
playwright received such a prestigious accolade ‘for his cartography of
structures of power and his trenchant images of the individual's resistance,
revolt, and defeat’.”

